    <!-- Guide Section -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
            <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
                <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-gray-800">The Ultimate Guide to Using Hashtags on Instagram and TikTok</h2>
                
                <!-- Why Hashtags Matter -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-8 mb-8 custom-shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 flex items-center">
                        <i class="fas fa-lightbulb text-yellow-500 mr-3"></i>
                        Why Hashtags Matter for Social Media Success
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        Hashtags are more than just trendy additions to your postsâ€”they're powerful tools that can dramatically increase your content's discoverability and engagement. On platforms like Instagram and TikTok, hashtags function as a categorization system that helps users find content related to specific topics, interests, or communities.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                        When you include relevant hashtags in your posts, you're essentially creating doorways that allow new audiences to discover your content. This increased visibility can lead to more likes, comments, shares, and followers, ultimately boosting your social media presence and influence.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Instagram Strategy -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-8 mb-8 custom-shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 flex items-center">
                        <i class="fab fa-instagram text-pink-500 mr-3"></i>
                        Instagram Hashtag Strategy: Best Practices
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        Instagram allows up to 30 hashtags per post, but quantity doesn't always equal quality. Research suggests that posts with 9-12 hashtags tend to perform best in terms of engagement. When crafting your Instagram hashtag strategy, consider these best practices:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-green-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                            <span><strong>Mix hashtag sizes:</strong> Include a combination of popular (1M+ posts), moderately popular (100K-1M posts), and niche (less than 100K posts) hashtags to maximize your reach while ensuring your content doesn't get lost in oversaturated categories.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-green-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                            <span><strong>Use location-based hashtags:</strong> If your content is relevant to a specific location, include location-based hashtags to attract local audiences.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-green-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                            <span><strong>Create a branded hashtag:</strong> Develop a unique hashtag for your brand or campaign to encourage user-generated content and build community.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-green-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                            <span><strong>Research competitors:</strong> Analyze the hashtags used by successful accounts in your niche to identify effective hashtag strategies.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-green-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                            <span><strong>Update your hashtags regularly:</strong> Avoid using the same set of hashtags for every post. Rotate through different hashtag combinations to reach diverse audiences and prevent being flagged as spam.</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <!-- TikTok Strategy -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-8 mb-8 custom-shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 flex items-center">
                        <i class="fab fa-tiktok text-black mr-3"></i>
                        TikTok Hashtag Strategy: What Works
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        TikTok's algorithm differs from Instagram's, and so does its approach to hashtags. While Instagram allows up to 30 hashtags, TikTok has a character limit for captions (including hashtags) of 100 characters. This means you need to be more strategic with your hashtag selection. Here's what works on TikTok:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-green-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                            <span><strong>Trending hashtags:</strong> TikTok's "Discover" page highlights trending hashtags and challenges. Including these in your content can significantly boost visibility.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-green-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                            <span><strong>Niche-specific hashtags:</strong> Use hashtags that are specific to your content category to reach users who are interested in your niche.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-green-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                            <span><strong>Broad and specific combination:</strong> Include a mix of broad hashtags (like #fyp or #foryoupage) and specific ones related to your content.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-green-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                            <span><strong>Participate in challenges:</strong> TikTok thrives on challenges. Using challenge-specific hashtags can help your content gain traction.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-green-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                            <span><strong>Quality over quantity:</strong> Due to character limitations, focus on 3-5 highly relevant hashtags rather than trying to include as many as possible.</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <!-- Science Behind Hashtags -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-8 mb-8 custom-shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 flex items-center">
                        <i class="fas fa-flask text-blue-500 mr-3"></i>
                        The Science Behind Effective Hashtag Selection
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        Selecting the right hashtags isn't just about popularityâ€”it's about relevance, timing, and strategic placement. Here's the science behind effective hashtag selection:
                    </p>
                    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                        <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Relevance is Key</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Always prioritize hashtags that accurately describe your content. Irrelevant hashtags might bring temporary traffic but can harm your account's credibility and algorithm performance in the long run.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Hashtag Competition</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Extremely popular hashtags (with millions of posts) are highly competitive, making it difficult for your content to stand out. The sweet spot often lies in moderately popular hashtags that balance visibility with competition.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Timing Considerations</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Some hashtags perform better at specific times or days. For instance, #MondayMotivation is most effective on Mondays, while #WeekendVibes works best on weekends.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Hashtag Analytics</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Regularly analyze which hashtags drive the most engagement for your content and refine your strategy accordingly using platform insights and third-party analytics tools.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Common Mistakes -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-8 mb-8 custom-shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 flex items-center">
                        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle text-yellow-500 mr-3"></i>
                        Common Hashtag Mistakes to Avoid
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        Even with the best intentions, creators often make hashtag mistakes that can limit their content's potential. Here are some common pitfalls to avoid:
                    </p>
                    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                        <div class="bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-red-500">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800 mb-2 flex items-center">
                                <i class="fas fa-times-circle mr-2"></i>Using banned hashtags
                            </h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-red-700">Some hashtags have been banned or restricted by platforms due to association with inappropriate content. Using these can limit your content's reach.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-red-500">
